+# SDS Engine — Journal Compaction
+
+## 5. Logic
+
+- **Journal Snapshots and Compaction (FR-E83):**
+  - `state_snapshot` (`snapshot_version: 1`) stores full replay state, covered
+    logical events, duplicate count, and `events_covered`.
+  - Replay validates snapshot versions, seeds from the latest supported
+    snapshot, then applies only suffix records. Older pre-snapshot records are
+    ignored during replay.
+  - Manual compaction (`runs compact`) rejects live runs and malformed non-tail
+    journals before writing.
+  - Shared compaction sequence: replay current journal, write
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp`, fsync tmp, copy current journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`,
+    then atomic rename over `journal.jsonl`.
+  - Engine auto-compaction uses an explicit self-active allowance and runs only
+    after top-level node completion when post-snapshot count exceeds
+    `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events`.
