+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal Snapshots and Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** The durable run journal supports in-band `state_snapshot`
+  records and crash-safe compaction. Replay seeds from the latest supported
+  snapshot, applies only later journal events, and remains byte-equivalent to
+  full replay for the same logical run model.
+- **Tasks:** [REF:task:2026-06-journal-snapshots-compaction | journal-snapshots-compaction]
+- **Status:** [x]
+- **Motivation:** Long runs grow `journal.jsonl` without bound. Replay cost
+  should be bounded by a compact suffix while preserving the FR-E69 durability
+  contract and plain JSONL format.
+- Contract:
+  - `state_snapshot` payload carries `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete
+    replay model (`RunState`, covered logical events, duplicate count), and
+    `events_covered`.
+  - Replay of journals without snapshots is unchanged.
+  - Any snapshot version greater than supported fails replay clearly with the
+    journal path and version.
+  - Compaction protocol is fixed: replay current journal; write
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp` with one snapshot and zero tail events; fsync tmp;
+    copy current journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`; atomically rename tmp over
+    `journal.jsonl`.
+  - Manual compaction refuses live runs and journals that fail replay beyond
+    normal torn-tail tolerance. Engine auto-compaction may compact its own
+    active run only at top-level node completion boundaries.
+  - `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events` is a non-negative integer;
+    `0` disables auto-compaction; default is `1000`.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - [x] Snapshot replay, forward-version refusal, full-vs-snapshot
+    equivalence, suffix-only parsing, and torn-tail tolerance are covered.
+    Evidence: `lifecycle-replay_test.ts` snapshot/compaction cases.
+  - [x] Crash-injection covers every protocol boundary and leaves a replayable
+    journal. Evidence:
+    `lifecycle-replay_test.ts::journal compaction crash injection preserves replayable journal`.
+  - [x] Manual refusal rules and one-generation backup are covered. Evidence:
+    `lifecycle-replay_test.ts::journal compaction refuses live and malformed runs`;
+    `lifecycle-replay_test.ts::journal compaction keeps one backup and reports event and byte counts`.
+  - [x] Threshold validation, defaulting, and drift prevention are covered.
+    Evidence:
+    `config_test.ts::parseConfig validates journal_compaction_threshold_events`;
+    `merge_defaults_test.ts::mergeDefaults — workflow-only defaults do not leak into node settings`.
+  - [x] Engine auto-compaction runs at node completion boundaries and emits a
+    verbose line. Evidence:
+    `engine_test.ts::Engine.run auto-compacts only at node completion boundaries`.
+  - [x] CLI `runs compact` dry-run, summary format, help, and one-line errors
+    are covered. Evidence: `cli_test.ts::runs compact help and argument parsing`;
+    `cli_compact_test.ts`.
