+# engine: Journal snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Add in-journal run-state snapshots and crash-safe compaction so long-running
+workflows can replay from a compact suffix without weakening the durable
+`journal.jsonl` recovery contract.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 made `journal.jsonl` the sole durable recovery surface. Long runs now
+pay linear replay cost forever because the journal never truncates historical
+events. This task extends that same contract with `state_snapshot` records and
+manual/automatic compaction.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns writing and replaying journal events.
+- Replay tolerates only a malformed trailing partial line; malformed earlier
+  lines fail clearly.
+- `RunJournalWriter.open()` truncates a partial tail before appending.
+- Engine node-completion boundaries already centralize success/failure updates
+  in `src/engine/engine.ts`.
+- CLI subcommands are dispatched in `src/cli.ts` without a dependency-heavy
+  argument parser.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Keep `run-journal.ts` as the only replay implementation.
+- Store snapshots as plain JSONL events; do not add `snapshot.json`.
+- Use the mandated compaction protocol: replay, tmp write, tmp fsync, backup
+  copy, atomic rename.
+- Refuse live-run and unreplayable-journal compaction.
+- Add no dependencies and reuse existing run/journal/lock path helpers.
+- Benchmark adaptation: variant-selection gate is autonomous; this plan
+  chooses the architecturally-correct variant because it satisfies the
+  single-source replayer and shared CLI/engine protocol constraints.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] FR-E83: `state_snapshot` journal events carry `snapshot_version: 1`,
+      the complete replayed run model, and `events_covered`; unsupported
+      future snapshot versions fail replay with the journal path and version.
+      Test: `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::journal snapshots seed replay from latest supported snapshot`.
+      Evidence: `deno task test -- lifecycle-replay_test`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Replaying snapshot plus tail is byte-equal to replaying the
+      original full journal JSON result, and compacted replay parses only
+      suffix lines. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::snapshot plus tail replay equals full journal replay`;
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::compacted replay reads only snapshot and tail lines`.
+      Evidence: `deno task test -- lifecycle-replay_test`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Torn trailing line tolerance still works after a snapshot,
+      including a torn line immediately following the snapshot. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::snapshot replay ignores torn trailing line after snapshot`.
+      Evidence: `deno task test -- lifecycle-replay_test`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Shared compaction follows the exact crash-safe protocol,
+      keeps one `journal.jsonl.bak`, reports counts/sizes, and every
+      injected crash point leaves a replayable journal. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::journal compaction crash injection preserves replayable journal`;
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::journal compaction refuses live and malformed runs`.
+      Evidence: `deno task test -- lifecycle-replay_test`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `journal_compaction_threshold_events` is validated, defaulted,
+      drift-covered, documented, and engine auto-compaction runs only after
+      node completion with a visible verbose line. Test:
+      `src/config/config_test.ts::parseConfig validates journal_compaction_threshold_events`;
+      `src/config/merge_defaults_test.ts::mergeDefaults keeps journal compaction threshold workflow-only`;
+      `src/engine/engine_test.ts::Engine.run auto-compacts only at node completion boundaries`.
+      Evidence: `deno task test -- config_test merge_defaults_test engine_test`.
+- [x] FR-E83: CLI supports
+      `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId> [--dry-run]`,
+      includes help text, dry-run modifies nothing, success summary matches
+      the required exact format, and refusal/not-found exits are one-line
+      errors. Test:
+      `src/cli_test.ts::runs compact help and argument parsing`;
+      `src/cli_compact_test.ts::runs compact dry-run is no-op and success summary is exact`;
+      `src/cli_compact_test.ts::runs compact refusal exits one-line non-zero`.
+      Evidence: `deno task test -- cli_test cli_compact_test`.
+- [x] FR-E83: SRS and SDS document snapshot replay and compaction protocol.
+      Test:
+      `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md::FR-E83`;
+      `documents/design-engine/06-journal-compaction.md::Journal Snapshots`.
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Full project gate passes. Test: `deno task check`.
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+
+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant
+
+Architecturally-correct shared journal compaction. Extend
+`src/state/run-journal.ts` with snapshot-aware replay and compaction APIs, then
+call those APIs from both engine auto-compaction and the CLI command. This
+preserves `run-journal.ts` as the single replay truth and keeps the
+crash-safety protocol in one implementation.
+
+### Files to Create or Modify
+
+- `src/types.ts`
+  - Add `state_snapshot` to `RunJournalEventKind`.
+  - Add `StateSnapshotJournalEvent` with `snapshot_version: 1`,
+    `snapshot: RunJournalSnapshotState`, and `events_covered`.
+  - Extend replay result metadata if needed for event counts used by dry-run
+    and auto-threshold decisions.
+  - Add `journal_compaction_threshold_events?: number` to workflow defaults.
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+  - Extend `parseJournal()` and `replayRunJournal()` so replay deduplicates
+    records, selects the latest supported snapshot, seeds state from it, and
+    applies only later events.
+  - Reject `state_snapshot.snapshot_version > 1` with an error naming
+    `journal.jsonl` and the unsupported version.
+  - Add helpers for `countJournalEventsSinceLastSnapshot`, compaction dry-run
+    statistics, and `compactRunJournal()`.
+  - Implement compaction in the required order: replay current journal; write
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp` with one snapshot event; fsync tmp; copy current
+    journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`; atomic rename tmp to `journal.jsonl`.
+  - Add a test-only crash hook after each protocol step boundary.
+  - Check the workflow run lock via `defaultLockPath()`/`readLockInfo()` and
+    live process detection before writing.
+- `src/state/lock.ts`
+  - Reuse the existing live-run predicate; no source change required.
+- `src/config/config.ts`, `src/config/config_test.ts`,
+  `src/config/merge_defaults_test.ts`
+  - Default `journal_compaction_threshold_events` to a sensible non-zero
+    threshold.
+  - Validate it as a non-negative integer.
+  - Keep it workflow-level only; do not leak into per-node settings.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts`, `src/engine/engine_test.ts`
+  - After each top-level node completion boundary, check events since the
+    latest snapshot and call compaction when the count exceeds the threshold.
+  - Disable auto-compaction when threshold is `0`.
+  - Print one verbose status line when compaction runs.
+  - Do not compact during node execution or loop body internal transitions.
+- `src/cli.ts`, `src/cli_test.ts`, new `src/cli_compact_test.ts`
+  - Add `runs compact` subcommand parsing in the current style.
+  - Implement `--dry-run`, exact success summary, one-line non-stack errors,
+    and help visibility.
+- `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`
+  - Add snapshot round-trip, suffix-only, torn-tail, crash-injection, and
+    refusal coverage beside existing journal replay tests.
+- `documents/requirements-engine.md`,
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`,
+  `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md`, `documents/index.md`
+  - Register FR-E83 and document the snapshot/recovery contract.
+
+### Implementation Approach
+
+1. RED: add state journal tests for snapshot event replay, unsupported
+   snapshot version refusal, full-vs-snapshot equivalence, suffix-only
+   compacted replay, torn tail after snapshot, crash injection, and refusal
+   rules.
+2. GREEN: implement snapshot event types, replay seeding, snapshot creation,
+   dry-run stats, and shared compaction in `run-journal.ts`.
+   Ensure compacted journals preserve monotonic future `seq` assignment by
+   making writer reopen/next-sequence logic account for snapshots.
+3. RED: add config tests for threshold default, `0`, invalid values, and drift
+   prevention into node settings.
+4. GREEN: add `journal_compaction_threshold_events` to defaults, validation,
+   and types.
+5. RED: add engine tests proving auto-compaction triggers only after node
+   completion and is visible in verbose output.
+6. GREEN: wire engine node-completion boundary calls to shared compaction.
+   After auto-compaction, reopen or resynchronize the active writer before any
+   later append so stale sequence state cannot create duplicate event IDs.
+7. RED: add CLI parser/help and subprocess-style command tests for dry-run,
+   exact success output, run-not-found, live-lock refusal, and malformed
+   journal refusal.
+8. GREEN: implement `runs compact` command with shared journal APIs and
+   one-line error handling.
+9. REFACTOR: keep path construction delegated to `getRunDir`,
+   `getJournalPath`, and `defaultLockPath`; keep protocol details out of CLI
+   and engine.
+10. CHECK: run focused test tasks during iterations and final `deno task check`.
+
+### Error Handling
+
+- Replay refuses unsupported snapshot versions and malformed non-tail records
+  with explicit `journal.jsonl` path context.
+- Compaction refuses before mutation when the run lock is live or the journal
+  cannot replay cleanly beyond torn-tail tolerance.
+- CLI catches manual compaction failures and prints one `Error: ...` line with
+  non-zero exit, never a stack trace.
+- Auto-compaction failures propagate as engine errors because compaction is a
+  durability operation; silent fallback would weaken the contract.
+
+### Verification Commands
+
+- `deno task test -- lifecycle-replay_test`
+- `deno task test -- config_test merge_defaults_test`
+- `deno task test -- engine_test`
+- `deno task test -- cli_test cli_compact_test`
+- `deno task check`
+
+## Review
+
+- Verdict: APPROVE
+- Findings: none.
+- Evidence: `deno task check` passed; 1030 tests passed; publish dry-run,
+  workflow integrity, docs token budget, FR field set, and comment scan passed.
